<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Forever</title>
    <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/style.css' />
</head>
<body>
<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-1.11.2.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-migrate-1.2.1.min.js"></script>
<!-- Latest compiled and minified CSS -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.2/css/bootstrap.min.css">
<div id="banner" class="row page-header">
    <div class="col-md-12">
        <div>
            <h1 style="margin-left:5px">Forever</h1>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4" style="float:right;margin-left:10px">
            <div id="userbox">
                {{#signedIn}}
                    <a href="/profile">Profile</a>
                {{/signedIn}}
                {{^signedIn}}
                    <a href="/login">Login</a>
                    <a href="/register">Register</a>
                {{/signedIn}}
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div id="body" class="row" style="margin-left:15px;">
    <div class="col-md-8">
        <div>
            <h3 style="margin-left:5px;">What is this?</h4>
                <p style="margin-left:35px;">
                  Permanent, continual and redundant storage of data in a completely public format. Forever can be used to memorialize an entire person's life or even a mass-storage device for any documents you like.
                </p>
        </div>
        <br>
        <div>
            <h3 style="margin-left:5px;">Why?</h4>
                <p style="margin-left:35px;">
                    Data is important and is only becoming more important. Paying one price today to have your data exist for eternity is a small price.
                </p>
        </div>
        <br>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h3>Ready?</h3>
        <div>
            <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="/records">Upload something!</a>
        </div>
        <br>
    </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>
